  "prompt": "Is brain transplant true?",
  "response": "As of now, there has not been a successful human brain transplant. While the concept has been explored in science fiction and theoretical discussions, the complexity of the brain and its connection to the nervous system makes such a procedure immensely challenging and currently beyond our medical capabilities.\n\nThere have been experiments with brain transplants in animals, particularly in studies involving lower animals, but these have not been successfully replicated in higher mammals or humans. Most neurological functions and identity are closely tied to the entire nervous system, making the idea of transplanting just the brain problematic.\n\nInstead of a brain transplant, researchers are focusing on treatments for brain conditions through other means, such as stem cell therapy, neuroprosthetics, and various types of neurological rehabilitation.",
